> Mki$ wants to write a 2 Byte string and Mkl$ wants to write a 4 byte
> string...But I only want to write 64 in the file ! There`s no special
command
> for it? How do I do this? HELP please....

You can use the byte equivalents of the mki$ family which would be:

Print chr$(x) ; Write unsigned byte x to the file

y.w = Asc(inkey$(1)) ; Reads unsigned byte y from file into word variable

The only problem I can see with this is blitz's handling of signed and
unsigned bytes. If your variable y is of type byte then values greater than
128 will get a negative value whereas if y is of type word then it should be
a positivie value. I havn't tested this too much but I think its right :)

