  Well it all comes from the old RedCode Simulator. These are
programming contests in assem, with a controlling program that executed
an instruction from each program in turn. They tried to wipe each other
out by either randomly trashing memory, or being defensive and copying
itself from location to location etc. A program that was too complex
could get wasted by a simpler program because the complex one took too
long to execute it's main loop! I think there's a Redcode Simulator for
the Amiga.
  This is where viruses originated, because someone wondered what would
happen if the controlling program wasn't there anymore.... 
 
