>My program is using few quite big DIMs inside. In few parts of them I've
>to clear all items.

Ummm, try re dimming it, with the same size, that should clear it. If not
simply dim it with 0 items, and then re dim it the required size...I think
that should be the quickest way...plus, if your using them inside (and
not outside of statements...ie local to the statement) then you should
probably dim it to 0 items before your statement exits...as some people
suggested that local dim's aren't freed at the end of a statement/function!

>how can I make something like that b=a (I dont want use b\x=a\x and go
>on)

It depends, probably the fastest way would be

Copymem_ &a,&b,Sizeof .own

This should copy the contents of a to b. Be warned that this works only
for simple newtypes. You can't use it on newtypes that contain strings,
as this would not copy them, but use the same string for both, and would
cause you no end of trouble!. But you'd be alright with others (ie, you
can have .b .w .l .q .f and fixed arrays[] without any problems, but no
strings!). You could also write a function to do it faster, but for small
newtypes, you be better off using 

b\x=a\x,a\y,a\a

Just because there's not much data to shift!


Hope that helps,

Dave

