Yes, all of these.  Well, you don't need the font's NAME, but you must know
it's height.  Also, be aware that a listview always opens to show an even
number of text lines so it may open a bit less than your requested height.

To make it open at the exact innerheight of a window, I calculate the
listview's height in text lines, then adjust the window height to fit to this,
it is not possible to accurately do this the other way.

