   Yes, while the aforementioned static array would work quite well,
   I think a dynamically managed list (not the BLITZ list, rather our
   own linked-list) would be the best method for both maximum
   flexibility as well as speed.

   This way, you simply have two lists:  The "inactive" list which
   contains the objects currently NOT on screen and a second "active"
   list which contains all objects currently on screen.

   Objects would simply pass from one list to another as they enter/
   exit the visible display.

   All objects present in the "active" list would be processed in the
   collision-detection system.

   This would limit the usefulness of such a collision detection system
   as only those people who use the active/inactive system of object
   management would fully benefit from the collision routine, but
   any serious project is probably already using such a system.

