allowed up to 7 parameters which are passed in d0-d6, and that any
other ones can be access via -(a2) or -(a7) - ie they are on the
stack.

Now i've checked my routine thoroughly and even right at the start, at
entry point, blitz has shuffled the last to parameters. Parameter 7 is
coming to me via the stack, and parameter 8 is coming to me via
register d6. It should be the other way around I would have thought.
